	   <tr><td colspan=2>Another good point about DEX often forgotten or most of the time not even realized is that the higher your DEX is the more you hit in the upper range of your damage spectrum. <br><br>In other words High STR means higher MAX (Along with level etc...) AND <br>High DEX means the more you hit near your MAX. <br><br>DEX also affects damage MAX with ranged weapons like STR does with melee weapons. <br><br>DEX also affects how often one Procs or hit Crits/Crips. <br><br>Put my words to the test if you don't believe me. Think back to the last time an enchanter cast "Boon" on you... Not only did you proc and crit more but you also hit more hits in the upper range of your damage spectrum. <br><br>The Moral to the story is DEX is good. This is nice secondary weapon. <br><br>Vanhin<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
